						               													<description>In the Puzzle Detective game, you must solve crimes by jigsawing different clues. When you get to a crime scene, you have to pull a puzzle piece with stolen goods from the bag. This is your first clue. You put the stolen goods in front of you and hurry on to the next crime scene. You can find the thief in the line of suspects by dragging event cards on your way between the various crime scenes. When you find the thief, you puzzle the thief together with the stolen goods. You need a thief and at least two stolen items of the same color to finish the game. For now, you should quickly get to the right crime scene and get the last clue to complete your investigation. The one who first has a complete chain of evidence of puzzle pieces in front of him; a thief + at least two stolen goods + a crime scene in the same suit are the winners of the game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
